# Sake — Japanese rice brewing, grades and vocabulary (A-tier).

def "sake:sake" "日本酒 — rice wine brewed with koji mould and yeast (清酒)."
ln sake:sake beverage:fermented thesaurus:related
ln sake:sake foodsci:koji thesaurus:related
ln sake:sake cuisine:japanese thesaurus:related

def "sake:junmai" "Pure-rice sake, no added alcohol — full, rice-forward (純米)."
ln sake:junmai sake:sake sake:grade
def "sake:honjozo" "A touch of distilled alcohol added — light, easy (本醸造)."
ln sake:honjozo sake:sake sake:grade
def "sake:ginjo" "Premium: rice polished ≤60%, fragrant and refined (吟醸)."
ln sake:ginjo sake:sake sake:grade
def "sake:daiginjo" "Top grade: rice polished ≤50%, delicate and aromatic (大吟醸)."
ln sake:daiginjo sake:sake sake:grade
def "sake:nigori" "Cloudy, coarsely-filtered sake — sweet, creamy (にごり)."
ln sake:nigori sake:sake sake:grade
def "sake:namazake" "Unpasteurised, fresh and lively (生酒)."
ln sake:namazake sake:sake sake:grade
def "sake:koshu" "Aged sake — amber, rich (古酒)."
ln sake:koshu sake:sake sake:grade

def "sake:seimaibuai" "Rice-polishing ratio — how much grain remains; lower = finer (精米歩合)."
ln sake:seimaibuai sake:sake thesaurus:related
def "sake:koji_sake" "Aspergillus mould that saccharifies the rice — the heart of brewing (麹)."
ln sake:koji_sake sake:sake thesaurus:related
ln sake:koji_sake foodsci:koji thesaurus:related
ln sake:koji_sake foodsci:fermentation_science thesaurus:related
def "sake:toji" "The master brewer (杜氏)."
ln sake:toji sake:sake thesaurus:related
def "sake:kura" "A sake brewery (蔵元)."
ln sake:kura sake:sake thesaurus:related
def "sake:nihonshu_do" "Sake Meter Value — the dry/sweet scale (日本酒度)."
ln sake:nihonshu_do sake:sake thesaurus:related
def "sake:kimoto" "A traditional, labour-intensive starter method — rich, acidic."
ln sake:kimoto sake:sake thesaurus:related
def "sake:warmed_sake" "Sake served warm (燗) vs chilled (冷や)."
ln sake:warmed_sake sake:sake thesaurus:related
